<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 21 at 3:12PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of western Wilcox,
southern Dooly, Sumter and Crisp Counties through 400 PM EDT...
At 311 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Arabi, or 7 miles south
of Cordele, moving north at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Americus, Cordele, Vienna, Arabi, Pineview, Leslie, Pitts, De Soto,
Desoto, Cobb, Sumter, Lamar, Richwood, New Era, Huntington, Seville,
Drayton, Pleasant View, Methvins and Tippettville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
